text:
vidcontrol has no error code other than when it prints a usage
message. This makes it difficult to test via scripts. The attached
code adds error codes. 

Caution is advised as the changes have not fully been tested.

Fix: 

55a56,64
> enum  error_code { OKAY = 0, 
>                       BADMODECODE   = 1,  SCRNMAPNOT    = 2,
>                       SCRNMAPBAD    = 3,  FONTFILENOT   = 4, 
>                       FONTSIZEBAD   = 5,  FONTFILEBAD   = 6,
>                       SCRNSVR_POS   = 7,  CURSORBADARG  = 8,  
>                       CONS_BADNUM   = 9,  CONS_OUTRANGE = 10, 
>                       CONS_ACTIVATE = 11, MOUSEBADARG   = 12,  
>                       MOUSEBADARG2  = 13, SHOW_ADP_FAIL = 14,
>                       SHOWBADARG    = 15 };
